BBC.Later.with.Jools.Holland.S45E08.1080i.h264-NX

BBC 2 HD 7th Nov 2014
11:50pm to 00:50am S45E08 Recorded

Joining Jools in the studio is English singer-songwriter Bryan Ferry performing tracks from his upcoming solo album, Avonmore. English rock musician Paul Rodgers, former frontman of Free and Bad Company, plays numbers from The Royal Sessions, his recent Memphis soul album which was recorded at Willie Mitchell's revered Royal Studios. From Philadelphia, indie rock outfit The War on Drugs play tracks from their third album, Lost in a Dream. From south London, the infectious afrobeat sounds of Fuse ODG with a couple of numbers from his debut album, T.I.N.A. Swedish newcomer Seinabo Sey debuts her soulful electro pop and also making her debut is hotly tipped Bath singer-songwriter Laura Doggett. Plus Jools chats to Pink Floyd's David Gilmour about the inspiration behind their forthcoming and final album, The Endless River.
